    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term referring to unrelated brownish birds with red breasts, one a thrush, the American robin (Turdus migratorius), and the other a flycatcher, the European robin (Erithacus rubecula).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
